bNav"></span><span style=3D"font-size:0"></span><h2>How Car Insurance Is Ca=
lculated &amp; Price Factors</h2></div><div id=3D"mg-page-content-3101370" =
class=3D"page-content" style=3D"column-count:1;margin-bottom:20px"><p>Insur=
ance companies use several factors to estimate your risk of filing a claim.=
 Since each company weighs these factors differently, rates can vary dramat=
ically for the same coverage.</p></div><div id=3D"mg-page-headline-1766581"=
 class=3D"inline-block w-full"><h3>Your Car Insurance Company</h3></div><di=
v id=3D"mg-page-content-3101371" class=3D"page-content" style=3D"column-cou=
nt:1;margin-bottom:20px"><p>Your car insurance company choice is the bigges=
t factor in what you pay. The same 40-year-old driver with good credit and =
no violations pays $97 monthly with Travelers but $215 with AIG. That's an =
$118 difference for identical coverage. Comparing car insurance quotes from=
 several companies for identical coverage &nbsp;is your best strategy to sa=
ve.</p>
<p>Why the gap? Car insurance companies measure the risk of insuring you di=
fferently based on your profile. Regional insurers have lower overhead cost=
s, and companies offering specialized policies like pay-per-mile insurance =
can pass those savings along. Insurers also offer different discount struct=
ures that can reduce your rate by 5% to 40%.</p></div><div class=3D""><div =
id=3D"mg-db-subtitle-table-28985"><div class=3D"font-mg-header uppercase te=
xt-sm font-light leading-[1.4285714285714286] mg-desktop-start:font-bold mg=
